        <br>
        <div class="row new-row">
          <div class="col-md-8">
            <h1><span class="smaller">What's <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sentiment_analysis" target="_blank">sentiment analysis</a>?</span></h1>
            <h3>Sentiment analysis is a way of processing text to understand the attitude and emotions of a writer.</h3>
            <p class="lead">
              There are two main ways to analyze a document for sentiment. The first measures a negative, positive, or neutral attitude.
              This is called the <span class="font-bold">polarity</span> of a text.
            </p>
            <p class="lead">
              The second looks at the language to see whether the writer use an objective or subjective tone. This is called the <span class="font-bold">subjectivity</span> of a text.
            </p>
            <p>If you want to learn more about sentiment analysis, <a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/~liub/FBS/NLP-handbook-sentiment-analysis.pdf" target="_blank">read this</a>.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-4">
