            <iframe class="embed-responsive-item" width="100%" height="400" frameborder="0" scrolling="yes" src="//plot.ly/~zcaceres/4.embed"></iframe>
              <h3>High polarity indicates a "positive affective state" by the writer.</h3>
              <p class="lead">In this case, Plato's <span class="font-semi-bold">Symposium</span> is the clear winner.</p>
              <p class="lead"> The most neutral (least-polarized)? Arch-rationalist Bertrand Russell's <span class="font-semi-bold">The Analysis of Mind</span></p>
            </div>
