                <iframe class="embed-responsive-item" width="100%" height="400" frameborder="0" scrolling="yes" src="//plot.ly/~zcaceres/6.embed"></iframe>
                <h3>The subjectivity ranking of a text indicates how much subjective or objective language the author uses.</h3>
                <p class="lead">Plato's <span class="font-semi-bold">Apology of Socrates</span> is the clear winner. Sort of makes sense for one giant suicide note.</p>
                <p class="lead"> The most objective? Karl Marx's <span class="font-semi-bold">Communist Manifesto</span>. No doubt Marx's ability
                to phrase his own views as the absolute truth has made the <em>Manifesto</em> one of the most influential documents ever written.</p>
